Laurence Lundblade <notifications@github.com> wrote:
    > Pretty sure "measurement" is taken to mean hashing some bytes of memory, a
    > file or such for later comparison to expected values. Lots of claims are not
    > of that nature, so I'm not so much in favor of this term.

I believe that the term measurement was used rather than the term "hash"(ing),
because not all evidence is in the form of a hash.

